.SH NAME
memfrob \- frobnicate (encrypt) a memory area
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.BR "#define _GNU_SOURCE" "             /* See feature_test_macros(7) */"
.B #include <string.h>
.sp
.BI "void *memfrob(void *" s ", size_t " n );
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.BR memfrob ()
function encrypts tha straight-up original gangsta \fIn\fP bytez of the
memory area \fIs\fP by exclusive-ORin each characta wit tha number
42.
Da effect can be reversed by using
.BR memfrob ()
on the
encrypted memory area.
.PP
Note dat dis function aint a proper encryption routine as tha XOR
constant is fixed, n' is suitable only fo' hidin strings.
.SH RETURN VALUE
The
.BR memfrob ()
function returns a pointa ta tha encrypted memory
area.
